Module com.example.sudoku
Package com.example.sudoku.utils

Class Path

java.lang.Object
com.example.sudoku.utils.Path
public class Path extends Object
Utility class that contains the paths to the various resources used in the Sudoku application. These paths include the locations of FXML files, CSS files, and other resources required to load views and stylesheets in the application.

Note: The constants in this class point to the resources, and it is recommended to replace the static string constants with an Enum for better type safety and organization in the future.

    GAME_VIEW

    static final String
    START_VIEW
    The path to the StartView FXML file, which is the main screen where the user starts the game.
    static final String
    STYLE_START_VIEW
    The path to the stylesheet for the StartView, used for styling the main screen of the game.
    static final String
    TRY_AGAIN_VIEW
    The path to the TryAgainView FXML file, which is shown when the player finishes the game, either to retry or view the results.
